<div id="Thmexercise1" class="ltx_theorem ltx_theorem_exercise">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_title_theorem"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_theorem"><span class="ltx_text ltx_font_bold">Exercise 1</span></span> (Continuous Indicator).</h6>
<div id="Thmexercise1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Consider a metric space <math id="Thmexercise1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="(E,d)" display="inline"><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>E</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>d</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></math>. For <math id="Thmexercise1.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="x\in E" display="inline"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>E</mi></mrow></math> and <math id="Thmexercise1.p1.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="B\subseteq E" display="inline"><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>âŠ†</mo><mi>E</mi></mrow></math>, define</p>
<table id="S0.Ex1" class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table">

<tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_align_center"><math id="S0.Ex1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="d(x,B):=\inf\{d(x,y)\colon y\in B\}." display="block"><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>:=</mo><mrow><mo movablelimits="false">inf</mo><mo>â¡</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">}</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr>
</table>
<ol id="S0.I1" class="ltx_enumerate">
<li id="S0.I1.i1" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">1.</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i1.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">If <math id="S0.I1.i1.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="d(x,B)=0" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></math>, then <math id="S0.I1.i1.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="x\in\bar{B}" display="inline"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mover accent="true"><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">Â¯</mo></mover></mrow></math>, the closure of <math id="S0.I1.i1.p1.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="B" display="inline"><mi>B</mi></math>.</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_proof">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_font_italic ltx_title_proof">Solution.</h6>
<div id="S0.I1.i1.p2" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Assume that <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="x\in\bar{B}^{c}" display="inline"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">Â¯</mo></mover><mi>c</mi></msup></mrow></math>. By definition</p>
<table id="S0.EGx1" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex2"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex2.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle\bar{B}=\smashoperator[]{\bigcap_{A\supseteq B\text{ closed}}^{}}A" display="inline"><mrow><mover accent="true"><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">Â¯</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle="true"><munder><mo largeop="true" mathsize="160%" movablelimits="false" stretchy="false" symmetric="true">â‹‚</mo><mpadded lspace="-26.2pt" width="0.0pt"><mi>A</mi><mo>âŠ‡</mo><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mtext>Â closed</mtext></mrow></mpadded></munder></mstyle><mi>A</mi></mrow></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>
<p class="ltx_p">we have</p>
<table id="S0.EGx2" class="ltx_equationgroup ltx_eqn_align ltx_eqn_table">

<tbody id="S0.Ex3"><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_td ltx_align_right ltx_eqn_cell"><math id="S0.Ex3.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\displaystyle x\in\bar{B}^{c}=\smashoperator[]{\bigcup_{A\supseteq B\text{ %&#10;closed}}^{}}A^{c}=\smashoperator[r]{\bigcup_{O\subseteq B^{c}\text{ open}}^{}}O." display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">Â¯</mo></mover><mi>c</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle="true"><munder><mo largeop="true" mathsize="160%" movablelimits="false" stretchy="false" symmetric="true">â‹ƒ</mo><mpadded lspace="-26.2pt" width="0.0pt"><mi>A</mi><mo>âŠ‡</mo><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mtext>Â closed</mtext></mrow></mpadded></munder></mstyle><msup><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msup></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mpadded lspace="16.5pt" width="+16.5pt"><mstyle displaystyle="true"><munder><mo largeop="true" mathsize="160%" movablelimits="false" stretchy="false" symmetric="true">â‹ƒ</mo><mpadded lspace="-22.5pt" width="0.0pt"><mi>O</mi><mo>âŠ†</mo><mrow><msup><mi>B</mi><mi>c</mi></msup><mo>â¢</mo><mtext>Â open</mtext></mrow></mpadded></munder></mstyle></mpadded><mi>O</mi></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></math></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>
<p class="ltx_p">So by the definition of open sets, there exists <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\epsilon&gt;0" display="inline"><mrow><mi>Ïµ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></math>, such
that <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="B_{\epsilon}(x)\subseteq O\subseteq B^{c}" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mi>Ïµ</mi></msub><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>âŠ†</mo><mi>O</mi><mo>âŠ†</mo><msup><mi>B</mi><mi>c</mi></msup></mrow></math> for some
open set <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m4" class="ltx_Math" alttext="O" display="inline"><mi>O</mi></math>. So we have for any <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m5" class="ltx_Math" alttext="y\in B" display="inline"><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></math>, <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m6" class="ltx_Math" alttext="d(x,y)&gt;\epsilon" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Ïµ</mi></mrow></math>.
Therefore <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m7" class="ltx_Math" alttext="d(x,B)&gt;\epsilon&gt;0" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Ïµ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></math>. So for all <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m8" class="ltx_Math" alttext="d(x,B)=0" display="inline"><mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></math> we
necessarily have <math id="S0.I1.i1.p2.m9" class="ltx_Math" alttext="x\in\bar{B}" display="inline"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mover accent="true"><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy="false">Â¯</mo></mover></mrow></math>.
âˆ</p>
</div>
</div></li>
<li id="S0.I1.i2" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">2.</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i2.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">Suppose that <math id="S0.I1.i2.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="B\neq\emptyset" display="inline"><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>â‰ </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ…</mi></mrow></math>. Prove that</p>
