<li id="S0.I1.i3" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_item">3.</span> 
<div id="S0.I1.i3.p1" class="ltx_para ltx_noindent">
<p class="ltx_p">Let <math id="S0.I1.i3.p1.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="A\subseteq E" display="inline"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>âŠ†</mo><mi>E</mi></mrow></math> be <span class="ltx_text ltx_font_bold">closed</span>. Show that, for any
<math id="S0.I1.i3.p1.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\epsilon&gt;0" display="inline"><mrow><mi>Ïµ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></math>, the function</p>
<table id="S0.Ex9" class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table">

<tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_align_center"><math id="S0.Ex9.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="f_{A}^{\epsilon}(x)=\left(1-d(x,A)/\epsilon\right)^{+}" display="block"><mrow><mrow><msubsup><mi>f</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>Ïµ</mi></msubsup><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>/</mo><mi>Ïµ</mi></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></math></td>
