<div class="ltx_proof">
<h6 class="ltx_title ltx_runin ltx_font_italic ltx_title_proof">Solution.</h6>
<div id="S0.I2.i5.p2" class="ltx_para">
<p class="ltx_p">We know from <span class="ltx_ref ltx_ref_self"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">2</span></span> that <math id="S0.I2.i5.p2.m1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="g_{1}:x\mapsto d(x,A)" display="inline"><mrow><msub><mi>g</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>â†¦</mo><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>â¢</mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></math> is <math id="S0.I2.i5.p2.m2" class="ltx_Math" alttext="1" display="inline"><mn>1</mn></math>-Lipschitz. The same is true for <math id="S0.I2.i5.p2.m3" class="ltx_Math" alttext="g_{3}:x\mapsto(1-x)^{+}" display="inline"><mrow><msub><mi>g</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>â†¦</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></mrow></math>.
Because <math id="S0.I2.i5.p2.m4" class="ltx_Math" alttext="g_{2}:x\to\tfrac{x}{\varepsilon}" display="inline"><mrow><msub><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>â†’</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>Îµ</mi></mfrac></mrow></mrow></math> is <math id="S0.I2.i5.p2.m5" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\frac{1}{\varepsilon}" display="inline"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>Îµ</mi></mfrac></math>-Lipschitz we
